title: Two construction workers injured in fall from scaffolding
text:
Two construction workers were injured in a fall from scaffolding at a Seattle apartment building Friday.
Medics were called to the building at 111 Sixth Avenue at 10:52 a.m.
Seattle fire said the men fell about 20 feet.
Video from Chopper 7 showed one man on a stretcher.
Both men were transported to Harborview with minor injuries.
